> TY :=3D UnivariateTaylorSeries(Fraction Integer,'y,0)
> TX :=3D UnivariateTaylorSeries(TY,'x,0)
> sx :=3D taylor(sin(x+y),x=3D0)
> coeffs :=3D [taylor(t,y=3D0)::TY for t in coefficients sx]
> s :=3D series(coeffs)$TX
>
> That looks a bit complicated, but can you have that in another CAS? Serie=
s
> with coefficients being series themselves? And these are no finite object=
s.
> You can ask the resulting series for any coefficient you like.
